How to compile and load IRmega firmware
=======================================

To compile and load the IRmega firmware into MattairTech's MT-DB-U4 module
under Windows XP:

 - Install the WinAVR, Atmel's Flip and LUFA from the following URLs:

	http://winavr.sourceforge.net/index.html
	http://www.atmel.com/dyn/products/tools_card.asp?tool_id=3886
	http://www.fourwalledcubicle.com/LUFA.php

 - Copy the InfraRed folder from this archive into LUFA library's folder
   Demos\Device\LowLevel

 - Connect MT-DB-U4 module to PC using USB cable, enable bootloader by
   HWB jumper and press RESET button. You should see LED blinking.

 - Configure Flip and check the MCU is online

 - Go to the Demos\Device\LowLevel\InfraRed folder and execute the
  'recompile.bat' script, or run:

	> make all
	> make flip

